title: Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.17 Dortmund, Germany (Remaster)
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1980.06.17 Dortmund, Germany   

Led Zeppelin
Westfalenhalle, Dortmund, Germany
June 17th, 1980
SBD-Main AUD-Patching
Complete Show 104 minutes 13 seconds

SBD Source - SBD 1st Gen-DAT1-2CDR1>Remaster
AUD Source - 1stGenCassette>DAT Unknown>Remaster

Live Omega Series #1

Winstons Disclaimer: Remastering is just a Hobby.. 
take it and enjoy or just pass on it. The choice is 
yours. This version is never meant to be definitive.

Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist:

D1T01 - Train Kept a Rollin
D1T02 - Nobodys Fault But Mine
D1T03 - Black Dog
D1T04 - In The Evening
D1T05 - Rain Song
D1T06 - Hot Dog
D1T07 - All My Love
D1T08 - Trampled Underfoot
D1T09 - Since Ive Been Loving You
D2T01 - Achilles Last Stand
D2T02 - White Summer
D2T03 - Black Mountainside
D2T04 - Kashmir
D2T05 - Stairway To Heaven
D2T06 - Rock and Roll
D2T07 - Whole Lotta Love

Winston Remasters - 2015

Comments: 
The first show of the 1980 Tour and a very dynamic and good one. 
Jimmy, as always on this tour, flashes between brilliance (Since 
I've Been Loving You, Stairway To Heaven) and mistakes 
(White Summer/Black Mountain Side). The encores are great, 
especially Heartbreaker inside of Whole Lotta Love ... a treat!
